{{italic title}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Jesus: Apocalyptic Prophet of the New Millennium | image = Jesus Apocalyptic Prophet of the New Millennium.jpg | author =[[Bart D. Ehrman]] | country = United States | language = English | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | release_date = [[:Category:1999 books|1999 books]] | media_type = Print (hardback) | pages = 368 | genre = [[Christian history]], [[Biblical criticism]] | isbn = 978-0195124743 }} '''''Jesus: Apocalyptic Prophet of the New Millennium''''' is a 1999 book by leading New Testament scholar [[Bart D. Ehrman]]. In it, he argues that Jesus was an [[Apocalypse|apocalyptic]] preacher, i.e., his main message was that the end of history was near, that God would shortly intervene to overthrow evil and establish his rule on earth, and that [[Jesus]] and his disciples all believed these end time events would occur in their lifetimes. Ehrman also analyses New Testament passages such as Jesus' supposed birth in Bethlehem of a virgin and finds them not historically credible.<ref name=Kirkus>{{cite web|title=Jesus: Apocalyptic Prophet of the New Millennium|url=https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/bart-ehrman/jesus-apocalypic-prophet-of-the-new-millennium/|publisher=Kirkus Reviews|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=PW>{{cite web|title=Jesus: Apocalyptic Prophet of the New Millennium|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-19-512473-6|publisher=Publisher's Weekly|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=Ehrman>{{cite book|last=Ehrman|first=Bart D.|title=Jesus: Apocalyptic Prophet of the New Millennium|date=1999|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0195124743}}</ref>
