'''Octave Hamelin''' (July 22, 1856 in [[Montpellier]] – September 11, 1907 in [[Prades, Pyrénées-Orientales]]) was a [[France|French]] [[philosopher]]. He taught as a [[professor]] at the [[University of Bordeaux]] (1884-) and the [[University of Sorbonne]] (1905-). Hamelin was a close friend of the sociologist [[Émile Durkheim]], with whom he shared an interest in the French philosopher [[Charles Renouvier]]. He is also known as a translator of [[ancient philosophy|classical Greek philosophers]].
